ZH: 我不知道你需要我原谅你的什么。
EN: I don't know what you need me to forgive you for.

ZH: 我原谅了她的错误，但是我不能忘记。
EN: I forgive her mistake, but I can't forget.

ZH: 请原谅我的冒犯。
EN: Please forgive my offense.

ZH: 昨天他道了歉，希望我原谅他。
EN: He apologized yesterday, hoping I would forgive him.

ZH: 无论发生什么事情，我都会原谅你。
EN: No matter what happens, I will forgive you.

ZH: 他们终于原谅了彼此，重归于好。
EN: They finally forgave each other and made up.

ZH: 请原谅我在场的无礼行为。
EN: Please forgive my rude behavior.

ZH: 我真的很抱歉，请原谅我。
EN: I'm really sorry, please forgive me.

ZH: 只有通过原谅别人，我们才会得到内心的平静。
EN: Only by forgiving others can we find peace within ourselves.

ZH: 原谅别人是一种品质。
EN: Forgiving others is a virtue.

ZH: 请你原谅我的自私。
EN: Please forgive my selfishness.

ZH: 昨晚我们发生了争执，但是现在我们已经互相原谅了。
EN: We had a quarrel last night, but now we have forgiven each other.

ZH: 原谅是一种解脱。
EN: Forgiveness is a form of liberation.

ZH: 他不愿意原谅那个背叛了他的朋友。
EN: He is not willing to forgive the friend who betrayed him.

ZH: 原谅不是忘记，而是选择放下。
EN: Forgiveness is not forgetting, but choosing to let go.

ZH: 无论犯了什么错，我都会原谅你。
EN: No matter what mistake you've made, I will forgive you.

ZH: 她真心地向他道歉，请求原谅。
EN: She sincerely apologized to him and asked for forgiveness.

ZH: 让我们共同努力，尝试原谅过去的伤害。
EN: Let's work together to try to forgive past hurts.

ZH: 请原谅我不能来参加你的生日派对。
EN: Please forgive me for not being able to attend your birthday party.

ZH: 他学会了原谅他人的过失。
EN: He learned to forgive others' mistakes.
